-- ============================================================================
-- 0138 — Wrap auth.uid() / auth.jwt() / auth.role() in (select …) in RLS policies
--
-- Audit item #13 from the 2026-06-04 perf review. The classic Supabase RLS
-- perf footgun: bare auth.uid() is re-evaluated per row by the planner,
-- but (select auth.uid()) is hoisted to a single scalar evaluation per
-- statement. On a 100k-row matches scan this is ~50x speedup on RLS-
-- filtered reads. Generated by sweeping pg_policies and rewriting the 77
-- policies that had unwrapped occurrences (pre-filtered to skip those with
-- any already-wrapped instance — preventing double-wrap).
--
-- Semantics identical: auth.* are STABLE; (select …) is hoisted by the
-- planner so the function still runs exactly once per statement.
-- ============================================================================

ALTER POLICY "ai_chat_select_self" ON public.ai_chat_messages
